CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1941, pg.1 reads: Flew In For A Short Visit - attractive Rose Rolls, 21-year-old aviatrix who flew here from Institute W. Va. Tuesday afternoon with Marshall Fields of Pittsburgh who is a student at W. Va. State college. Miss Rolls is one fo [of] the few Negro women pilots in country. She has been flying for the past three years.  A former student at W. Va. State, she is now employed there as a business secretary.  She returned to Institute Wednesday afternoon with Mr. Fields.  Picture was taken upon their arrival at Bettis Field. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Rose Rolls waving out window of small plane with "...RD CASTO" inscribed on side
